SP.P:
Made his Will; and by that Will made you his heyre;
with this prouiso, that as occasion shall hereafter moue him;
hee may reuoke or alter it when he pleases.

My life he seekes. I would he had it since he has de∣priu'd
mee of those blessings that should make mee loue it;
Come; I'le giue it him.

O were my body circumuolu'd within that cloude;
that when the thunder teares his passage open, it might scatter
me to nothing in the ayre!

I haue bethought me of a better way.—Nephew;
we must conferre.—Sir; I am growne a wondrous Studi∣ent
now o'late. My wit has reach'd beyond the scope of Na∣ture;
yet for all my learning I am still to seeke, from whence
the peace of conscience should proceede.
